n E. subgibbosa largely depends on pollinators, although it showed some degree of autogamy. Autonomous pollination was unfeasible in E. chilensis, which depended on ﬂower visitors for its reproductive success. Both E. chilensis var. albidiﬂora and E. curvispina var. mutabilis showed some degree of autogamy.},
	language = {en},
	urldate = {2020-04-29},
	journal = {PeerJ},
	author = {Guerrero, P. C. and Antinao, C. A. and Vergara-Meriño, B. and Villagra, C. A. and Carvallo, G. O.},
	month = oct,
	year = {2019},
	pages = {e7865},
	file = {Guerrero et al. - 2019 - Bees may drive the reproduction of four sympatric .pdf:files/713/Guerrero et al. - 2019 - Bees may drive the reproduction of four sympatric .pdf:application/pdf}
