hrough pollination, because seeds of A. cumingii were dispersed less than 2 m away from a parent plant. Presumably, restricted gene ﬂow could enhance genetic divergence between populations on slopes of contrasting aspects. This factor could be important in contributing to the high diversity and endemism in the Chilean Andes.},
